04/12/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The Security Council convened on Sunday (December 3rd) to discuss issues related to Macedonia's bid for NATO membership and related reforms. 
President Branko Crvenkovski said afterwards that they found the messages from last week's NATO summit in Riga both positive and demanding. 
He said Council members agreed that a political consensus is needed to complete judicial sector restructuring and curb organised crime and corruption. 
.
In other news, a Skopje court has ordered 30-days detention for ten of the 19 people arrested last week in a large-scale operation against corruption and organised crime. 
The list of detainees reportedly includes former government officials. 
(Vecer - 04/12/06; A1 TV, Makfax, Telma TV - 03/12/06)
